* With his head bowed D entered the Iron Fist right behind Fenox, his 
shoulder brushing against her back as he turned slightly to look behind him 
and then to the side to look at the metal walls.
This was just lik the ship he knew before, only that it didn't have the warm 
musty smell of humans in it. More of a rusty smell was what this one smelled 
like at one sniff, probably because people in metal lived here instead.
D's ears moved in ever direction, taking in the sounds of computer consoles 
and the constant humm of systems as they worked. This was a noisy world!
He turned his head and looked back towards Fenox, wondering just what she 
was going to show him and if he had ever seen anything similar.
In this ship, there were bound to be wonders.
D bumped his cheek against her shoulder for a sign to move on, eager to find 
out more.*
